I have fired it with winchester low recoil low noise target loads. I really don't want to sell it but bills need to be payed...It functions fine. The magazine has a stop in it for hunting laws but it can be removed to add more shells. Although, it seems to be known on the internet as the "widowmaker" because of the way the gun was designed. I have never heard of anyone being killed by one but I need to say not to shoot it. The gun was made in 1898. The serial numbers on the barrel and reciever do not match as was standard for marlin at the time. Low 4 digit serials. It does not have the patented hang fire saftey release button that was added on to the gun in 1899. That makes this gun rare. The ATF says this is not a firearm! As such, it can be shipped to most states without an FFL!

title: For Sale:  Kimber Super America .308 Rifle In "SUPER" 2017 SHOT Show Auction
postcontent:
This one-of-a-kind Kimber SuperAmerica .308 rifle, featuring hand engraving and “SUPER308” serial number is one of two Kimber firearms being featured for the first time in the history of the SHOT Show auction. Featured in a separate SHOT Show auction on GunBroker.com is a Kimber Super Match II 1911 with matching engraving and Serial number “SUPER1911”.The special pair not only marks the first time that Kimber firearms have been featured in the SHOT Show auction, it is also the first time that a themed handgun and rifle have ever been offered by one manufacturer. The rifle and pistol share the “SUPER” serial number theme to emphasize their “Super” status among target shooters, hunters and collectors.This SHOT Show SuperAmerica was hand-engraved by Rob Bunting of Baron Engraving in Trumbull, CT. Rob has engraved several of the most successful guns in the history of the SHOT Show auction. Commenting on the engraving patterns he selected for the SUPERAMERICA, Rob said, “This pattern has a very strong central spine with leaves placed more formally at regular intervals. The spine receives very little shading; the leaves are heavily shaded, and cross-hatched, which creates a very strong contrast in the design. I also removed a fair amount of background from between the scrolls and put a nice strong punch dot pattern down to increase the contrast. Black fill in the cuts makes the whole thing pull together and pop.
The Kimber SUPERAMERICA Traditional rifle offers an extraordinary combination of design and performance features that provide classic bolt-action elegance, reliability, accuracy and light weight. This .308 features a highly polished 22-inch barrel with match-grade chamber and is guaranteed to shoot sub-MOA. Stock is hand-rubbed AAA- grade walnut with ebony forearm tip. Pillar and glass bedding insure accuracy and strength. Five shot capacity with an overall length of 41.25” and weight of only 5 pounds and 10 ounces. This proven long-range rifle is fitted with a Nightforce 2.5 -10 X 42 NXS Compact Riflescope. The NXS is extolled for its streamlined proportions, minimal weight, and performance far beyond its size. The Nightforce NXS Compact has an objective lens assembly that focuses light rays more precisely for exceptional image clarity and color accuracy. The NXS 2.5-10x 42 Compact combines a versatile magnification range with a large exit pupil for fast target acquisition.Nightforce Optics has received major awards from Outdoor Life, Sporting Classics and other experts in the hunting and shooting sports media. Their rugged, reliable repeatability has been the subject of many press reviews and is a key reason demanding hunters, target shooters and tactical professionals have little problem in investing $2,000 or more for scopes like this Nightforce 2.5 -10 X 42 NXS Compact.The SHOT Show Auction is administered for the National Shooting Sports Foundation by the Hunting and Shooting Sports Heritage Trust.
